            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, pat your <strong>hake</strong> <strong>fillet[s] </strong>dry with kitchen paper and add to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray, then sprinkle the <strong>cheesy breadcrumb mix</strong> over the fish until totally covered</p><p>When the potatoes have 12-15 min left, put the tray in the oven until the breadcrumb mixture is starting to turn golden and the fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>cheesy baked hake</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1698922569009-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1698922569009-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1698922569009-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1698922569009-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1698922569009-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While everything's in the oven, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> and cook for 7-8 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]<strong> </span>cold<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>water </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1698922572515-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1698922572515-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1698922572515-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1698922572515-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1698922572515-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to the pan with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the peas are warmed through – these are your <strong>pea greens</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> to a small bowl with the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong>, the <strong>softened butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and mix until fully combined – this is your <strong>garlic butter</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1698922577885-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1698922577885-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1698922577885-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1698922577885-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1698922577885-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cheesy baked hake </strong>with the <strong>mini</strong> <strong>roast potatoes</strong> and<strong> pea greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Top the hake with the <strong>garlic butter</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the garlic butter or just add a little!</span></strong></p><p>Season with<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> to taste</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
